title = "Fear of Southern Influence."
description = "Several Northern officials and emirs worry that amalgamation may expose the North to Southern political ideas, Christianity, and Western education. Frederick Lugard reassures Northern leaders that indirect rule and traditional authority structures will remain protected under British administration."
